<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFEA293AF889FEDC091648D9" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEA293AF889FEDC0D484DC1" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF889FEDC0DDE4E04" bold="true" box="[199,466,294,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF993FEDD0EED4E05" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[477,737,295,321]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF993FEDD0EED4E05" box="[477,737,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFAA2FEDD0F204E05" box="[748,812,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
seems to be more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFCC5FEDD092C4E05" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1163,1312,295,321]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFCC5FEDD092C4E05" box="[1163,1312,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFDC6FEDD0D054E20" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFDC6FEDD0D054E20" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the absence of eyespots. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFB50FEB108114E21" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[798,1053,331,357]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFB50FEB108114E21" box="[798,1053,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFC6DFEB108514E21" box="[1059,1117,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the detailed morphology of trophi in common with 
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF9F8FE950E424ECD" box="[438,590,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF9F8FE950E464ECD" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[438,586,367,393]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">P. paradoxus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
While the ramus of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFB2CFE950FEE4ECD" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[866,994,367,393]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFB2CFE950FEE4ECD" box="[866,994,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFBA9FE95082E4ECD" box="[999,1058,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFC1BFE9508E94ECD" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1109,1253,367,393]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFC1BFE9508E94ECD" box="[1109,1253,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short caudal tip and is without a medial projection, that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFAE8FE690F394EE8" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[678,821,403,428]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFAE8FE690F394EE8" box="[678,821,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a long caudal tip and is with a medial projection. However, in spite of the resemblances as above, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFAF2FE4D0FB24E95" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[700,958,439,465]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFAF2FE4D0FB24E95" box="[700,958,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFB8BFE4D080D4E95" box="[965,1025,439,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be clearly distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFDC6FE4D0D014EB1" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFDC6FE4D0D014EB1" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characteristics: (1) 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFAEBFE210FA94EB1" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[677,933,475,501]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFAEBFE210FA94EB1" box="[677,933,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFBE5FE210FEA4EB1" box="[939,998,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has two ciliated buccal fields separated by a septum (upper and lower buccal fields, 
<figureCitation id="131B2A2CFFEA293AFACFFE050ED44D5D" box="[641,728,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[461,1127,1102,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[454,1133,1095,1885]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philodinavus koreanus n. sp. (a) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed, ventral view; (b) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) spurs and toes, dorsolateral view; (e) creeping, ventral view (scale bars: a–c = 20 μm; d = 10 μm; e = 25 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501199/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Figs. 1e</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="131B2A2CFFEA293AFB43FE050F204D5E" box="[781,812,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1528,1552]" captionTargetBox="[463,1125,669,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-243@4.[463,1125,669,1505]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Light microscopy photographs of Philodinavus koreanus n. sp. (a–b) creeping, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (e) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed; (f) scanning electron microscopy photograph of trophi, caudal view (× 6500); (g–h) trophi, cephalic view (scale bars: a–b = 50 μm; c–e = 25 μm; f = 2 μm; g–h = 10 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; m, manubrium; ma, major teeth; mi, minor teeth; r, ramus; ra, ramus apophysis; ro, rostrum; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501201/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">2b</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFBCAFE0508184D5D" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[900,1044,511,537]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFBCAFE0508184D5D" box="[900,1044,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only one, and (2) 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFD46FE050CF14D79" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFD46FE050CF14D79" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AF94AFDD90D4C4D79" box="[260,320,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a pair of thick and large as well as three pairs of small processes on the cheeks of lower buccal field (
<figureCitation id="131B2A2CFFEA293AF890FDBD0D524D26" box="[222,350,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[461,1127,1102,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[454,1133,1095,1885]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philodinavus koreanus n. sp. (a) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed, ventral view; (b) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) spurs and toes, dorsolateral view; (e) creeping, ventral view (scale bars: a–c = 20 μm; d = 10 μm; e = 25 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501199/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Figs. 1a, b</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF98EFDBD0E5A4D25" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[448,598,583,609]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF98EFDBD0E5A4D25" box="[448,598,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only one pair of processes on cheeks bordering single buccal field (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFEA293AF8D1FD910D3B4DC1" author="Murray, J." box="[159,311,618,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" pagination="367 - 386" refId="ref6620" refString="Murray, J. (1905) On a new family and twelve new species of Rotifera of the order Bdelloidea, collected by the Lake Survey. Transactions of the Royal Society of Edinburgh, 41, 367 - 386. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0080456800034451" type="journal article" year="1905">Murray 1905</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5F6621FFEA293AF8D9FA0208FE49E4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501201" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6501201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501201/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" startId="4.[151,250,1528,1552]" targetBox="[463,1125,669,1505]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEA293AF8D9FA0208FE49E4" blockId="4.[151,1437,1528,1696]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF8D9FA020D1F4954" bold="true" box="[151,275,1528,1552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Light microscopy photographs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFA3EFA020F544954" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[624,856,1528,1552]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFA3EFA020F544954" box="[624,856,1528,1552]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFB10FA030F984954" box="[862,916,1529,1552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(a–b) creeping, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (e) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed; (f) scanning electron microscopy photograph of trophi, caudal view (× 6500); (g–h) trophi, cephalic view (scale bars: a–b = 50 μm; c–e = 25 μm; f = 2 μm; g–h = 10 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; m, manubrium; ma, major teeth; mi, minor teeth; r, ramus; ra, ramus apophysis; ro, rostrum; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEA293AF889F935091648D9" blockId="4.[151,1436,1742,2021]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
In addition to the absence of eyespots and the difference in the trophi morphology as mentioned above, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF8D9F9080D9A4848" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,406,1778,1804]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF8D9F9080D9A4848" box="[151,406,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AF9D5F9090DDA4849" box="[411,470,1779,1805]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFB55F9090FAA4848" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[795,934,1779,1804]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFB55F9090FAA4848" box="[795,934,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characteristics: (1) the spurs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF8FAF8EC0DB84874" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[180,436,1814,1840]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF8FAF8EC0DB84874" box="[180,436,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AF9F7F8ED0DF84875" box="[441,500,1815,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have wide interspace, while those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFBDCF8ED08124874" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[914,1054,1815,1840]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFBDCF8ED08124874" box="[914,1054,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are without interspace, and (2) the uncus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF8B1F8C00E0C4810" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[255,512,1850,1876]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF8B1F8C00E0C4810" box="[255,512,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Philodinavus koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AFA49F8C10E4F4811" box="[519,579,1851,1877]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has 19–20 minor teeth, while that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFBA4F8C108744810" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[1002,1144,1851,1876]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFBA4F8C108744810" box="[1002,1144,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 17–20. Since 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFEA293AFD0BF8C00D09483D" author="Ricci, C. &amp; Shiel, R. J. &amp; Fontaneto, D. &amp; Melone, G." pageId="4" pageNumber="403" pagination="241 - 248" refId="ref6833" refString="Ricci, C., Shiel, R. J., Fontaneto, D. &amp; Melone, G. (2003) Bdelloid rotifers recorded from Australia with description of Philodinavus aussiensis n. sp. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 242, 241 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.1078 / 0044 - 5231 - 00101" type="journal article" year="2003">
Ricci 
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFDC6F8C10CB8483C" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
didn’t describe the morphology of ciliated buccal field of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AFBC4F8A5081A483C" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[906,1046,1887,1912]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFBC4F8A5081A483C" box="[906,1046,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the comparison of the buccal field between 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF8B5F8790D7148D8" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[251,381,1922,1948]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF8B5F8790D7148D8" box="[251,381,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEA293AF9CAF8790DCC48D9" box="[388,448,1923,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEA293AF9B8F8790E8F48D8" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[502,643,1923,1948]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF9B8F8790E8F48D8" box="[502,643,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be put on hold until further studies (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFEA293AFC00F878090248D9" author="Ricci, C. &amp; Shiel, R. J. &amp; Fontaneto, D. &amp; Melone, G." box="[1102,1294,1922,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" pagination="241 - 248" refId="ref6833" refString="Ricci, C., Shiel, R. J., Fontaneto, D. &amp; Melone, G. (2003) Bdelloid rotifers recorded from Australia with description of Philodinavus aussiensis n. sp. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 242, 241 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.1078 / 0044 - 5231 - 00101" type="journal article" year="2003">
Ricci 
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AFCDCF87908C748D8" box="[1170,1227,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFEA293BF889F85C0E394DC1" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEA293BF889F85C0E844EB1" blockId="4.[151,1436,1742,2021]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEA293AF889F85C0D554884" bold="true" box="[199,345,1958,1984]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Description.</emphasis>
Without eyespots. Rostrum much narrower than head; ratio of rostrum width to greatest head width about 1: 2.4. Rostral lamella bilobed and short; slightly wider than rostrum end width. Two, upper and lower, ciliated buccal field separated by thin and wavy septum; upper buccal field (ubf) enclosed by thick and wavy margin; lower buccal field with tree pairs of short projections anterolaterlly and a pair of paddle-shaped big projections posterolaterally (
<figureCitation id="131B2A2CFFEB293BF992FF250E134FBD" box="[476,543,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[461,1127,1102,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[454,1133,1095,1885]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philodinavus koreanus n. sp. (a) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed, ventral view; (b) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) spurs and toes, dorsolateral view; (e) creeping, ventral view (scale bars: a–c = 20 μm; d = 10 μm; e = 25 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501199/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); lower lip, posterior margin of lower buccal field, curly bracket-shaped (
<figureCitation id="131B2A2CFFEB293BFD21FF250CB84E5A" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[461,1127,1102,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[454,1133,1095,1885]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philodinavus koreanus n. sp. (a) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed, ventral view; (b) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) spurs and toes, dorsolateral view; (e) creeping, ventral view (scale bars: a–c = 20 μm; d = 10 μm; e = 25 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501199/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
). Trophi symmetrical (
<figureCitation id="131B2A2CFFEB293BF98CFEF90E384E5A" box="[450,564,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1528,1552]" captionTargetBox="[463,1125,669,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-243@4.[463,1125,669,1505]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Light microscopy photographs of Philodinavus koreanus n. sp. (a–b) creeping, ventral view; (c) head, trophi about to protrude from the lower buccal field, ventral view; (d) head, upper buccal field almost closed, ventral view; (e) head, upper buccal field somewhat closed; (f) scanning electron microscopy photograph of trophi, caudal view (× 6500); (g–h) trophi, cephalic view (scale bars: a–b = 50 μm; c–e = 25 μm; f = 2 μm; g–h = 10 μm). lbf, lower buccal field; m, manubrium; ma, major teeth; mi, minor teeth; r, ramus; ra, ramus apophysis; ro, rostrum; s, septum; tr, trophi; ubf, upper buccal field." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501201/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CD89B4CFFEB293BF9B5FEF90E1A4E5A" box="[507,534,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
–h
</figureCitation>
) and protrusible; uncus with three major teeth anteriorly and about 19–20 minor teeth including short teeth between major teeth; ramus without medial projection and with short caudal tip; manubrium arched, thin, wide anteriorly and tapering towards last minor teeth. Dorsal antenna short. Trunk stout and rather cylindrical. Foot short and with three pseudosegments; foot length about 1/6 of total body length. Spurs big, wide and horn-shaped; spur length about 1.5–1.7 times as long as spur base width; interspace slightly narrower than spur base width. Four toes short and with plump bases; ventral toes longer and bigger than dorsal ones; ventral toes about 1.47 times as long as dorsal ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEB293BF889FE050E394DC1" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF889FE050D724D5D" bold="true" box="[199,382,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length in creeping 139–200 μm. Greatest trunk width in creeping 23–44 μm. Trophi length 14–15 μm. Major teeth length 7.4–8.2 μm. Greatest major teeth width 0.86–0.93 μm. Minor teeth length 4.8–8.6 μm. Greatest minor teeth width 0.2–0.61 μm. Antenna length 6–9 μm. Spur length 10–14 μm. Ventral toe length 9 μm. Dorsal toe length 6 μm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFEB293BF889FD740FCF4DED" box="[199,963,654,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEB293BF889FD740FCF4DED" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" box="[199,963,654,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF889FD740D6D4DEC" bold="true" box="[199,353,654,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Distribution.</emphasis>
This new species is known only from its 
